{
  "page": "The Red Sowing (TV)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the event during the Dance of the Dragons, see <a href=\"/index.php/Sowing\" title=\"Sowing\">Sowing</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:rgb(248, 233, 208);border:none;\">\"The Red Sowing\"</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size: 100%\">\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:right;\">Season 2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">&#160;—&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:left;\">Episode 7</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"HOTD The Red Sowing.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ef/HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png/300px-HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ef/HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png/450px-HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ef/HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png/600px-HOTD_The_Red_Sowing.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original air date</th><td>\nJuly 28, 2024</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Running time</th><td>\n63 minutes</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Credits</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Directed by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loni_Peristere\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Loni Peristere\">Loni Peristere</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Written by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\nDavid Hancock</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Episode chronology</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">←&#160;Previous</th>\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">Next&#160;→</th>\n</tr><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk_(TV)\" title=\"Smallfolk (TV)\">Smallfolk</a>\"</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Queen_Who_Ever_Was\" title=\"The Queen Who Ever Was\">The Queen Who Ever Was</a>\"</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/List_of_House_of_the_Dragon_episodes\" title=\"List of House of the Dragon episodes\">List of episodes</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>\"<b>The Red Sowing</b>\" is the seventh episode of <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">season two</a> of the HBO <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/medieval_fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:medieval fantasy\">medieval fantasy</a> television series <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>. Running 63 minutes long, it premiered on July 28, 2024. The episode was written by David Hancock and directed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loni_Peristere\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Loni Peristere\">Loni Peristere</a>. Music was composed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramin_Djawadi\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ramin Djawadi\">Ramin Djawadi</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Official_synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Official synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Plot\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Plot</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Driftmark\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Driftmark</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Dragonstone\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dragonstone</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#King.27s_Landing\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">King's Landing</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Harrenhal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Harrenhal</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#The_Vale\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Vale</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Dragonmount\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dragonmount</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Cast\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cast</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Starring</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Co-starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Co-starring</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#Uncredited\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Uncredited</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Official_synopsis\">Official synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Official synopsis\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As Rhaenyra looks to gain an advantage by unusual means, Daemon pressures a young liege lord to raise up his bannermen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plot\">Plot</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Plot\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Differences_between_Fire_%26_Blood_and_House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon\">Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon</a></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Driftmark\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>On a beach <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> confronts <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Addam of Hull\">Addam of Hull</a> about his recent claiming of the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a>. Addam bends the knee to her and divulges that he does not know if he has the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">blood of the dragon</a> in him. Rhaenyra invites him to fly back to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> with her nonetheless.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dragonstone\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Rhaenyra's counsellors are worried about the idea of a <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">lowborn</a> man being able to ride a dragon but Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> shuts the debate down. Corlys later congratulates Addam in private and brings the news to his brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alyn of Hull\">Alyn of Hull</a>.\n</p><p>Rhaenyra and <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a> talk about Addam's parentage and his possible lack of Targaryen blood before Rhaenyra is convinced to seek her new <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonriders</a> amongst the smallfolk. She orders her handmaid in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Elinda_Massey\" title=\"Elinda Massey\">Elinda Massey</a>, to rally as much <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonseed\" title=\"Dragonseed\">dragonseeds</a> as she can find in the city.\n</p><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> confronts his mother about her recent decisions. Even though Jace knows he is a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a>, he feels his dragon was the proof in the eyes of many that he is a true Targaryen and that the accusations of bastardy laid against him and his brothers in the past had no validity. If anybody can ride a dragon, then Jace feels like his legitimacy might be questioned again as well as his status as Rhaenyra's heir. Jace is also afraid that these new dragonriders could turn against Rhaenyra. The queen hears her son's arguments but remains stern in her position, the dragonseeds will have their chance to claim a dragon.\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"King's_Landing\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"King.27s_Landing\">King's Landing</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: King&#039;s Landing\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> has her wound she received during the riot tended by Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a>. She remarks that just like her new scar nothing is clean in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>. She decides to go to the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">Kingswood</a> accompagnied by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rickard_Thorne\" title=\"Rickard Thorne\">Rickard Thorne</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> to resource herself.\n</p><p>News of Addam's exploit has reached the hears of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jasper_Wylde\" title=\"Jasper Wylde\">Jasper Wylde</a> though he is uncertain of its veracity. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> counsels against speaking of it to the Prince Regent, <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a>, as the two of them watch him stripping Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Martyn_Reyne\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Martyn Reyne\">Martyn Reyne</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Waters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eddard Waters\">Eddard Waters</a> of their white cloaks and sending them to the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>. \n</p><p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> has started physiotherapy to walk again with Orwyle at the behest of Larys Strong.\n</p><p>Rumors of Rhaenyra's search for dragonriders spread in the streets of King's Landing. <a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf</a> is relunctant to go despite his numerous boasts of being the bastard son of the late Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelon_Targaryen_(son_of_Jaehaerys_I)\" title=\"Baelon Targaryen (son of Jaehaerys I)\">Baelon the Brave</a>. His friends <a href=\"/index.php/Mujja\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mujja\">Mujja</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cley_(friend_of_Ulf)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cley (friend of Ulf)\">Cley</a> convinces him, however. Having recently lost his sick daughter and with no news of payment for his work, <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh</a> wants to go as well. <a href=\"/index.php/Kat\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kat\">Kat</a> tries to change her husband's mind but to no avail. Hugh reveals to her that contrary to what he told her in the past he did know his mother. She was a silver-headed <a href=\"/index.php/Prostitute\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prostitute\">prostitute</a> in a <a href=\"/index.php/Pleasure_house\" title=\"Pleasure house\">pleasure house</a> and the sister of Baelon the Brave (though not explicity stated, it is implied she was Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Saera_Targaryen\" title=\"Saera Targaryen\">Saera Targaryen</a>). During the night, the <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloak\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloak\">Gold cloaks</a> loyal to Mysaria help the dragonseeds recruited by Elinda to sneak away from the capital aboard Alyn's ship.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Harrenhal\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Oscar_Tully\" title=\"Oscar Tully\">Oscar Tully</a> and the riverlords have arrived to <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>. Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> pressures Oscar to rally the riverlords to fight for him. The young <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Trident\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Trident\">Lord Paramount of the Trident</a> is not so easily swayed as Daemon had hoped, he first wants to bring order in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and clean up the mess Daemon has made before supporting Rhaenyra. Confronted by his actions in front of the riverlords, Daemon is forced to execute Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Willem_Blackwood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Willem Blackwood\">Willem Blackwood</a> to appease Lord Oscar and his <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">bannermen</a>. Returning to his chambers Daemon has a vision of his brother, King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a>, offering him the <a href=\"/index.php/Crown\" title=\"Crown\">crown</a> but Daemon refuses to take it.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Vale\">The Vale</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Vale\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> and Rhaenyra's sons leave the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a> as Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Arryn\" title=\"Jeyne Arryn\">Jeyne Arryn</a> watches on. Rhaena decides to find the wild dragon on her own.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dragonmount\">Dragonmount</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dragonmount\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The gathered dragonseeds arrive on Dragonstone and are presented before Rhaenyra. The <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonkeepers\" title=\"Dragonkeepers\">dragonkeepers</a> refuse to help the bastards claiming dragons, Rhaenyra thus led them herself inside the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonmount\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragonmount\">Dragonmount</a> where the dragons reside. She calls after <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a> and make place for the first dragonseed, <a href=\"/index.php/Silver_Denys\" title=\"Silver Denys\">Silver Denys</a>, to try to claim him. Vermithor rejects Denys and burns him, chaos ensue amongst the seeds. Some are burnt, some are killed and some eaten by the dragon. Hugh saves the life of a fellow seed by redirecting Vermithor's attention on him. Facing the Bronze Fury, Hugh stands his ground and show no fear which the dragon respects. Hugh is able to calm and touch Vermithor, thus forming a bond. Looking from above, Rhaenyra is glad that she has found a new dragonrider. In the midst of all the commotion, Ulf is separated from the rest and walks down a passageway. He finds <a href=\"/index.php/Silverwing\" title=\"Silverwing\">Silverwing</a> sleeping in her lair but wakes her up when he walks on a clutch of eggs. Silverwing is intrigued and is docile with the newcomer. Ulf is able to climb on her saddle and fly away towards the capital for their first flight together. When alerted of the presence of a dragon above King's Landing, Aemond takes off on <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> and follows Silverwing and Ulf to Dragonstone. Seeing Vermithor, Silverwing and <a href=\"/index.php/Syrax\" title=\"Syrax\">Syrax</a> ready to engage, Aemond orders Vhagar to return home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e07.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e07.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cast\">Cast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Cast\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Starring\">Starring</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Red_Sowing_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Starring\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div style=\"column-count:2; column-width:300px;\"> \n<ul><li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matt_Smith\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matt Smith\">Matt Smith</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emma_D%27Arcy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Emma D&#39;Arcy\">Emma D'Arcy</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olivia_Cooke\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Olivia Cooke\">Olivia Cooke</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Toussaint\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Steve Toussaint\">Steve Toussaint</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonoya_Mizuno\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sonoya Mizuno\">Sonoya Mizuno</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matthew_Needham\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matthew Needham\">Matthew Needham</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Glynn-Carney\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tom Glynn-Carney\">Tom Glynn-Carney</a> as King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ewan_Mitchell\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ewan Mitchell\">Ewan Mitchell</a> as Prince <a href=\"/ind